Parliament, Wednesday, 5 May 2021 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow visit Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality as part of its oversight visit to Eastern Cape municipalities.
	
	The committee will receive a progress report from the municipality on the Auditor-General’s findings for the 2018/19 financial year, and on investigations that include the Special Investigating Unit reports.
	
	The committee will also meet with the Eastern Cape MEC of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs on the status of municipalities in the province.
	
	Details of the programme are as follows: 
	Date: Thursday, 6 May 2021
	Time: 18:00
	Venue: Nelson Mandela Bay City Hall
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	
